main event: A civilian observed a round object with flat sides in the SSW sky over Chicago for about 8 to 10 minutes on the night of May 27, 1966.
interesting points: The object was stationary and did not make any sound, trail, or exhaust during the observation., The observer described the object as being roughly the size of four planes., The object had gray-white lights on the top, bottom, and sides., The object was first noticed when the observer happened to look up at the sky., After a brief observation, the object disappeared when the observer turned to find it again.
sighted object: one round object with flat sides
